name: Seared Chuck Eye Steak
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '(8 ounce)', 'name': 'beef chuck steaks'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': 'sprigs', 'name': 'thyme'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'shallot'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'beef broth'}
steps: Pat steaks dry with a paper towel. Season generously with salt and pepper.. Heat oil in a skillet over high heat. Place steaks in the hot skillet and immediately turn down the heat to medium-high. Cook for 4 minutes. Turn steaks, add 1 tablespoon butter (or more as desired) and thyme sprigs to the pan, and cook for an additional 4 to 6 minutes, depending on your taste. Remove steaks from skillet and let rest, about 5 minutes.. Meanwhile, make pan sauce: remove skillet from heat. Quickly saute the garlic and shallot for 1 to 2 minutes in the skillet using residual heat. Return the skillet to medium-low heat and add beef broth. Bring to a boil and reduce for 3 minutes.. Remove pan from heat and whisk in remaining 2 tablespoons butter. Serve sauce over steaks.

name: Ultimate Tomahawk Steak
ingredients: {'quantity': '3 1/2', 'unit': 'pound tomahawk', 'name': 'rib eye steak'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '2 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}
steps: Remove steak from refrigerator and let stand at room temperature 30 minutes to an hour before cooking.. Preheat the grill to medium-high, 400 to 450 degrees F (200 to 230 degrees C). Sprinkle steak evenly and liberally on all sides with salt and black pepper.. Lightly coat grill grates with oil or grilling spray. Place steak on hot grates, and grill, undisturbed, until it releases easily from the grates, about 4 minutes. Flip, and repeat on the other side. Continue grilling, turning occasionally, until a thermometer inserted into the thickest portion of steak registers 125 degrees F (52 degrees C), 30 to 40 minutes.. Transfer steak to a cutting board; let rest 15 minutes. Run a knife along the inside edge of the bone to remove steak from the bone in 1 piece; slice against the grain to serve.

name: Parmesan Cheese Crisps
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Parmesan cheese'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper or a silicone baking mat.. Using a tablespoon, create 16 mounds of cheese, about 2 inches in diameter, spaced at least 1 inch apart, on the prepared baking sheet. Press down on the middle of each mound to make them evenly thick.. Bake in the preheated oven until cheese is completely melted and edges are browned, 4 to 6 minutes. Remove from the oven to cool for 15 minutes. Remove from baking sheet and store at room temperature in an air-tight container for up to 5 days.

name: Spicy Chicken Jerky in the Air Fryer
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(5 ounce)', 'name': 'boneless chicken breasts, cut into strips'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mojo criollo marinade (such as Goya®)'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'Cajun seasoning'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': '', 'name': 'wooden skewers'}
steps: Combine chicken strips, marinade, and Cajun seasoning in a resealable plastic bag. Refrigerate for 8 hours to overnight.. Measure skewers to fit across the air fryer basket, slightly overlapping the edge. Trim off excess length.. Preheat the air fryer to 180 degrees F (80 degrees C) for 10 minutes.. Thread chicken strips onto skewers, leaving room in between each strip, while the air fryer is preheating.. Air fry for 1 hour 15 minutes. Adjust cooking time as most air fryers have a maximum setting of 30 minutes. Rearrange the skewers during the reset time.. Increase temperature to 200 degrees F (95 degrees C) and air fry for an additional 15 minutes.. Remove strips to a paper towel-lined storage container. Seal. Allow to rest overnight before serving.

name: Turkish Eggs (Cilbir)
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Turkish or Greek yogurt, at room temperature'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'clove', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'freshly ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt, or to taste (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '2 ½', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'finely chopped fresh dill, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'stick', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'Aleppo chile flakes'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'smoked paprika'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chopped fresh parsley'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'diced jalapeno pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'salt (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'white vinegar, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'sea salt'}
steps: To make yogurt spread: Place yogurt in a medium bowl and grate in garlic; mix to combine. Season with pepper, salt, and cayenne. Add dill and mix thoroughly. Set aside at room temperature.. To make Aleppo butter: Melt butter in a saucepan over medium heat; heat until bubbles begin to burst. Add chile flakes, paprika, and cumin. Stir until color is uniform. Turn off heat and let spices infuse.. To make parsley and jalapeño oil: Grind parsley and jalapeño together in a mortar. Drizzle in olive oil and season with salt; stir to combine.. To make poached eggs: Fill a large saucepan with 2 to 3 inches of water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium-low, add vinegar, and keep water at a gentle simmer. Crack an egg into a small bowl, then gently slip egg into water, holding the bowl just above surface of water. Repeat with remaining eggs. Cook until whites are firm and yolks have thickened but are not hard, 2 1/2 to 3 minutes. Remove with a slotted spoon, pat dry on a kitchen towel, and place onto a warm plate.. Dollop yogurt mixture onto serving plates. Use the back of a spoon to spread yogurt, carving ridges into the top to catch oil. Drizzle some jalapeño oil. Top with eggs and 1 to 2 spoonfuls of Aleppo butter. Sprinkle sea salt on top.

name: Thick-Cut Bacon in the Oven
ingredients: {'quantity': '16', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'thick-cut bacon'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).. Line a rimmed baking sheet with aluminum foil and place a baking rack on top. Arrange bacon strips on the baking rack.. Bake in the preheated oven until crispy, 15 to 20 minutes.

name: Quick Keto Chocolate Mousse
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'cream cheese, softened'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'heavy cream'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'powdered zero-calorie sweetener (such as Swerve)'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'cocoa powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'salt'}

name: Oven Baked Pulled Ham
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '6 to 8 pound', 'name': 'ham'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'mustard'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'liquid smoke'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'brown sugar barbecue rub'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'barbecue sauce'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'apricot preserves'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 275 degrees F (135 degrees C). Stir mustard and liquid smoke together in a small bowl. Rub mustard mixture evenly over ham and sprinkle barbecue rub all over. Place ham in a large disposable pan or large deep pan lined with foil. Cover with foil.. Bake in the preheated oven for 2 hours.. Remove pan from oven. Increase oven temperature to 300 degrees F (150 degrees C). Stir barbecue sauce and apricot preserves together in a bowl; pour mixture over ham and spread evenly. Cover with foil.. Bake until a meat thermometer or instant-read thermometer inserted into the center of ham reads 205 degrees F (96 degrees C), 5 to 6 hours.  Let stand until ham is cool enough to handle, 10 to 15 minutes. Shred ham with 2 forks and toss with pan drippings.

name: Garlic Mashed Cauliflower
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'minced garlic'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'riced cauliflower'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'nutmeg'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chives'}
steps: Melt butter in a large skillet, over medium heat. Add minced garlic and cook until fragrant, about 30 seconds.. Stir in thawed, riced cauliflower, salt, pepper, and nutmeg. Add chicken broth and bring to a boil, stirring frequently.. Cook, covered, about 8 minutes, then remove cover and continue cooking and stirring until most of the liquid evaporates, an additional 5 to 8 minutes.. Use an immersion blender to purée cauliflower until smooth. If an immersion blender is not available, spoon cauliflower into a blender to purée. When smooth, place in a serving bowl and garnish with snipped chives.

name: How to Cook Bacon in the Oven
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(16 ounce) package', 'name': 'bacon'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.. Place bacon slices, one next to the other, on the prepared baking sheet.. Bake in the preheated oven for 15 to 20 minutes.. Remove from the oven to flip bacon slices with kitchen tongs and then return to the oven.. Bake until crispy, 15 to 20 minutes more. Thinner slices will need less time, about 20 minutes total. Drain on a plate lined with paper towels.. Enjoy!

name: 4-Ingredient Keto Peanut Butter Cookies
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'peanut butter'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'low-calorie natural sweetener (such as Swerve®)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'sugar-free vanilla extract'}
steps: Gather all ingredients. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.. Combine peanut butter, sweetener, egg, and vanilla extract in a bowl; mix well until a dough is formed.. Roll dough into 12 (1-inch) balls. Place on the prepared baking sheet and press down twice with a fork in a criss-cross pattern.. Bake in the preheated oven until edges are golden, 12 to 15 minutes.. Cool for 1 minute before transferring to a wire rack to cool completely.

name: Air Fryer Rib-Eye Steak
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'rib-eye steaks, cut 1 1/2- inch thick'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'reduced-sodium soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'grill seasoning (such as Montreal Steak Seasoning®)'}

name: Cheese Crisps
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper.. Shred generous amounts cheese.. Arrange cheese in 24 small heaps on the prepared baking sheets.. Bake in the preheated oven until golden brown, about 7 minutes. Cool for 5 to 10 minutes before removing from baking sheets.

name: 90-Second Keto Bread in a Mug
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'blanched almond flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'salt'}
steps: Microwave butter in a microwave-safe mug until melted, about 15 seconds. Swirl the mug to coat with butter.. Add almond flour, egg, baking powder, and salt to the mug; whisk until smooth.. Microwave on high until set, about 90 seconds. Let cool for 2 minutes before slicing.

name: Air Fryer Bacon
ingredients: {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '(16 ounce) package', 'name': 'bacon'}
steps: Preheat an air fryer to 390 degrees F (200 degrees C) according to manufacturer's instructions.. Lay bacon in the air fryer basket in a single layer; some overlap is okay.. Fry for 8 minutes. Flip and continue cooking until bacon is crisp, about 7 minutes more.. Transfer cooked bacon to a plate lined with paper towels to soak up excess grease.

name: Zucchini Pizza Bites
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'zucchini, sliced into ¼-inch thick rounds'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pizza sauce, or more to taste'}, {'quantity': '20', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'pepperoni, or more to taste'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded mozzarella cheese, or as needed'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'Italian seasoning, dried parsley, or oregano for sprinkling (Optional)'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.. Spread zucchini slices in 1 layer on the prepared baking sheet.. Bake in the preheated oven until zucchini is tender, about 15 minutes.. Spoon pizza sauce over each zucchini slice and top with pepperoni and mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle herbs over each.. Bake in the preheated oven until cheese is melted, about 5 minutes more.

name: Smoked Chicken Drumsticks
ingredients: {'quantity': '12', 'unit': '', 'name': 'chicken drumsticks'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'vegetable oil, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'BBQ rub'}
steps: Place drumsticks on a rack over a drip tray or baking sheet. Air-dry in the refrigerator, 8 hours to overnight.. Preheat an electric smoker to 275 degrees F (135 degrees C) and add wood chips according to manufacturer's instructions.. Brush drumsticks lightly with vegetable oil. Place drumsticks in a resealable plastic bag and sprinkle with the rub. Toss to coat evenly.. Place drumsticks on the rack in the smoker. Smoke until chicken has reached an internal temperature of 165 degrees F (74 degrees C), about 2 hours.

name: Ultimate Low-Carb Zucchini Lasagna
ingredients: {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'zucchinis, thinly sliced lengthwise'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground beef'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'low-carb marinara sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'salt, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried oregano'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) container', 'name': 'ricotta cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground nutmeg'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded mozzarella cheese'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'aluminum foil'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Grease an 8-inch square baking dish with cooking spray.. Pat dry zucchini slices with a paper towel to remove excess moisture. Set aside.. Heat olive oil in a saucepan over medium-high heat. Add ground beef; cook until browned, 5 to 8 minutes.. Add marinara sauce, 1 teaspoon salt, oregano, and pepper; simmer for 10 minutes. Set aside.. Combine ricotta cheese, egg, 1 teaspoon salt, and nutmeg in a bowl; mix well. Set aside.. Arrange one layer of zucchini slices in the prepared baking dish. Cover with 1/2 of the sauce. Add another layer of zucchini slices. Spread ricotta mixture on top. Sprinkle with 1/2 of the mozzarella cheese. Add another layer of zucchini slices; cover with remaining sauce and top with remaining mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese. Cover the baking dish with aluminum foil.. Bake in the preheated oven for 30 minutes. Remove aluminum foil and bake until top is golden, about 15 minutes more.

name: Keto Smothered Chicken Thighs
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '(8 ounce)', 'name': 'skin-on, bone-in chicken thighs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'bacon, cut into 1/2 inch pieces'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'low-sodium chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'sliced mushrooms'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'heavy whipping cream'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'green onions, white and green parts separated and sliced'}
steps: Gather all ingredients. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).. Season chicken thighs on all sides with paprika, salt, and pepper.. Cook bacon in a cast iron skillet or oven-safe pan over medium-high heat until browned, 4 to 5 minutes. Remove from skillet and drain on a paper towel-lined plate. Drain and discard excess grease from the skillet.. Return the skillet to medium heat and cook chicken thighs, skin-side down, for 3 to 4 minutes. Flip chicken over and place the skillet in the preheated oven.. Bake until chicken thighs are no longer pink at the bone and juices run clear, about 30 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted near the bone should read 165 degrees F (74 degrees C). Remove chicken to a plate and cover with foil to keep warm. Remove all but 2 tablespoons of drippings from the skillet.. Return the skillet to the stove over medium-high heat. Pour in chicken broth while whisking up brown bits from the bottom of the skillet. Add mushrooms and cook until soft, about 3 to 4 minutes. Pour in heavy whipping cream and whisk together until lightly simmering, then reduce heat to medium-low. Season with salt and pepper, if necessary.. Return chicken and any juices back into the skillet; top with bacon and green onions. Serve immediately, spooning sauce over chicken.

name: Easy Keto Alfredo Sauce
ingredients: {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, crushed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'heavy whipping cream'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '(4 ounce) package', 'name': 'cream cheese, softened'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'salt, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'ground nutmeg, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'ground white pepper, or to taste'}
steps: Gather the ingredients.. Melt butter in a medium saucepan over low heat. Add garlic and cook until fragrant, about 2 minutes.. Stir in heavy cream and cream cheese. Gradually add Parmesan cheese, stirring constantly until well incorporated and melted, about 5 to 7 minutes.. Stir in salt, nutmeg, and white pepper. The sauce will thicken as it cools.. Serve and enjoy.

name: Sous Vide "Poached" Eggs
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'cold eggs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper'}
steps: Fill a large pot with water and place a sous vide immersion cooker into the water. Set temperature to 167 degrees F (75 degrees C) according to manufacturer's instructions; allow 15 minutes for the water to heat.. Gently lower eggs into the water using a slotted spoon. Immediately set a kitchen timer for 13 minutes.. Remove eggs from water once timer is up and let cool for 3 minutes. Gently crack egg around the middle and peel top half of shell. Slide egg out into a small bowl or serve over toast. Season with salt and pepper.

name: Low-Carb Bacon Cheeseburger Casserole
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'ground beef'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'onion powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'cooked bacon, cut into pieces'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'heavy whipping cream'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(12 ounce) package', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Cook beef, garlic, and onion powder in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat, stirring often, until beef is browned and crumbly, 5 to 7 minutes. Drain and discard grease.. Transfer beef to a 9x13-inch casserole pan. Add cooked bacon and stir to combine; spread in an even layer.. Whisk eggs, cream, salt, and pepper together in a medium bowl until well combined. Stir in 3/4 of the Cheddar cheese. Pour mixture over beef in the casserole dish, then sprinkle remaining Cheddar over top.. Bake in the preheated oven until golden brown on top, 30 to 35 minutes.

name: Easy Air-Fried Chicken Breast
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce)', 'name': 'chicken breast'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder, or to taste'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}
steps: Preheat an air fryer to 360 degrees F (182 degrees C).. Brush both sides of chicken breast with olive oil; season with garlic powder, salt, and pepper on one side. Place chicken breast, seasoned-side down, into the air fryer basket and sprinkle the other side with garlic powder, salt, and pepper.. Cook in the preheated air fryer for 9 minutes. Flip chicken and continue cooking until no longer pink in the center and the juices run clear, about 9 more minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).. Transfer chicken breast to a plate and loosely cover with aluminum foil. Let rest for 5 minutes before serving.

name: Simple Cauliflower Keto Casserole
ingredients: {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'head', 'name': 'cauliflower florets'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'heavy cream'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).. Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil and cook cauliflower until tender but firm to the bite, about 10 minutes. Drain, then arrange cauliflower in a small casserole dish.. Combine Cheddar cheese, cream, salt, and pepper in a bowl. Cover cauliflower with cheese mixture.. Bake in the preheated oven until cheese is bubbly and golden brown, about 25 minutes.

name: Keto Margarita
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'ice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'fluid ounces', 'name': 'tequila'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'fluid ounce', 'name': 'lime juice'}, {'quantity': '2 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'low-calorie natural sweetener (such as Swerve®)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'coarse salt'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'lime wedges'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': '1 pint-sized Mason jar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'fluid ounces', 'name': 'orange-flavored sparkling water (such as La Croix®)'}
steps: Fill a shaker half-full with ice. Add tequila, lime juice, and sweetener to the shaker. Seal and shake vigorously until outside is frosted, 10 to 15 seconds.. Place salt on a plate. Run 1 lime wedge along the rim of the Mason jar. Press the rim down into salt. Fill the jar with ice cubes.. Strain margarita into the jar. Top with sparkling water; stir. Garnish with remaining lime wedge.

name: Low-Carb Keto Cheese Taco Shells
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Line two baking sheets with parchment paper or silicone mats.. Wrap the handle of a wooden spoon with aluminum foil. Balance between two tall cans.. Spread Cheddar cheese on the prepared baking sheets into four 6-inch circles placed 2 inches apart.. Bake in the preheated oven until cheese melts and is lightly brown, 6 to 8 minutes. Cool for 2 to 3 minutes. Lift with a spatula and drape over the wrapped wooden handle to make a taco shell shape. Cool until set, about 10 minutes.

name: Baked Lemon Butter Chicken Thighs
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter, divided'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'onion powder'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '(8 ounce)', 'name': 'skin-on, bone-in chicken thighs'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'fresh parsley, chopped'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).. Place 3 tablespoons butter in a microwave-safe bowl and heat in a microwave oven until melted, 1 to 2 minutes. Smash garlic cloves with the side of a chef's knife and add garlic to the warm butter. Stir in lemon juice and onion powder; set aside.. Sprinkle both sides of chicken thighs with salt and pepper. Heat remaining 1 tablespoon butter in a medium oven-safe skillet over medium-high heat. Brown chicken, skin-side down, for 3 to 4 minutes. Flip chicken over and brush skin with lemon-butter mixture. Pour remaining butter mixture into skillet and remove from heat.. Bake in the preheated oven until chicken is no longer pink at the bone and the juices run clear, about 30 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted near the bone should read 165 degrees F (74 degrees C). Brush skin every 10 minutes with pan juices.. Remove skillet from the oven and place chicken on a serving platter. Drizzle chicken with pan juices and garnish with parsley.

name: Chaffles with Almond Flour

steps: Whisk egg, almond flour, and baking powder together in a bowl. Stir in mozzarella cheese; set batter aside.. Preheat a waffle iron according to the manufacturer's instructions.. Spray both sides of the preheated waffle iron with cooking spray. Pour 1/2 of the batter onto the waffle iron and spread it out from the center with a spoon. Close the waffle maker and cook until chaffle reaches your desired doneness, about 3 minutes. Carefully lift chaffle out of the waffle iron and repeat with remaining batter. Allow chaffles to cool and crisp up, about 2 to 3 minutes.

name: Air Fryer Hamburgers

name: Keto Crème Brûlée
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg yolks'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'heavy whipping cream'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'low-calorie natural sweetener (such as Swerve®), divided'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C).. Whisk egg yolks and vanilla extract in a bowl until combined.. Pour heavy whipping cream and 1 tablespoon sweetener into a saucepan; heat, whisking continuously, over medium heat until it starts to simmer. Remove from heat; gradually add egg yolk mixture, whisking continuously, until well combined.. Divide mixture evenly between 4 ramekins and place them in a glass baking dish; pour in enough hot water to come halfway up the sides of the dish.. Bake in the preheated oven on the middle rack until set, about 30 minutes.. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon sweetener over each crème brûlée. name: 31 Keto Desserts to Curb Your Cravings
Sous Vide Egg Bites
ingredients: {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cottage cheese'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'heavy cream'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': '6 (4-ounce) mason jars'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'serving', 'name': 'cooking spray'}
steps: Fill a large pot with water and place a sous vide immersion cooker into the water. Set temperature to 170 degrees F (77 degrees C) according to manufacturer's directions.. Combine eggs, cottage cheese, heavy cream, and salt in a blender; mix until thoroughly blended, 15 to 20 seconds.. Spray mason jars with cooking spray. Divide egg mixture between each jar. Screw on the lids until just barely tightened. Do not over-tighten as the jars can burst in the hot water.. Submerge mason jars into the water bath and set timer for 55 minutes. When timer is up, remove jars to a cooling rack. If serving immediately, run a knife along the outer edge and invert onto a plate; you can also eat directly from the jar. Let any remaining jars cool, then refrigerate for up to 1 week.

name: Air Fryer Blackened Chicken Breasts
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground thyme'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cumin'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'onion powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(6 ounce)', 'name': 'skinless, boneless chicken breast halves'}
steps: Mix paprika, thyme, cumin, cayenne, onion powder, black pepper, and salt together in a bowl; transfer to a large plate.. Preheat the air fryer to 360 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Rub oil over each chicken breast until fully coated, then press into spice mixture until all sides are coated. Let sit for 5 minutes while the air fryer preheats. Place into the air fryer basket.. Air-fry chicken until no longer pink in the center and the juices run clear, about 20 minutes, flipping halfway through. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).. Transfer chicken to a plate and let rest for 5 minutes before serving.

name: Tuscan Pork Tenderloin
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'minced garlic'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'dried rosemary'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'dried oregano'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'pork tenderloin'}

An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read at least 145 degrees F (63 degrees C). Remove from the oven and let stand for 5 minutes before slicing.

name: Bacon on the Grill

steps: Preheat an outdoor grill for medium-low heat.. Line a large rimmed baking sheet with aluminum foil. Place a cooling rack on top. Place bacon on rack, making sure no pieces are overlapping.. Place baking sheet on the grill grate, close the lid, and cook for 12 minutes or until desired doneness. Transfer bacon to a paper towel-lined plate to absorb excess grease.

name: Keto Chicken Parmesan
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce)', 'name': 'skinless, boneless chicken breast'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'heavy whipping cream'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'pork rinds, crushed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'ounce', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'red pepper flakes (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Italian seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'ghee (clarified butter)'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': "jarred tomato sauce (such as Rao's®)"}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded mozzarella cheese'}
steps: Set the oven rack about 6 inches from the heat source and preheat the oven's broiler.. Slice chicken breast through the middle horizontally from one side to within 1/2 inch of the other side. Cover with tomato sauce; top with mozzarella cheese.. Broil until cheese is bubbling and barely browned, about 2 minutes.

name: Keto Chicken Crust Pizza

name: Baked Spaghetti Squash
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'spaghetti squash, halved and seeded'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly grease a baking sheet with olive oil. Place spaghetti squash, cut-side down, onto the baking sheet.. name: Air Fryer Beef Tenderloin

Allow to rest, uncovered, for at least 10 minutes before serving.

name: Creamy Keto Taco Soup with Ground Beef
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground beef'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped onion'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'cream cheese, softened'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(14.5 ounce) cans', 'name': 'beef broth'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(10 ounce) cans', 'name': 'diced tomatoes and green chiles (such as RO*TEL)'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'heavy cream'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'salt, or to taste'}

name: Best Keto Bread

name: What Are Fat Bombs? Should You Eat These Keto Snacks?
Low-Carb Almond Cinnamon Butter Cookies

name: Instant Pot Roasted Brussels Sprouts
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'whole Brussels sprouts'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'vegetable broth'}
steps: Turn on a multi-functional pressure cooker (such as Instant Pot) and select Sauté function. Heat olive oil in the pot; cook and stir onion in hot oil until translucent, about 2 minutes. name: Garlic Butter Smoked Shrimp
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'large shrimp, peeled and deveined'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Cajun seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'clove', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'red pepper flakes'}, {'quantity': '⅛', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'thin strips lemon peel'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'sprigs', 'name': 'fresh thyme'}
steps: Place shrimp in a resealable plastic bag. Sprinkle with Cajun seasoning and drizzle with olive oil; toss shrimp around in the bag to evenly distribute seasoning. Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.. Preheat a smoker to 250 degrees F (120 degrees C). Add wood chips according to manufacturer's instructions.. Place in the preheated smoker and cook shrimp until firm and orange-pink in color, about 30 minutes. Try not to overcook as the shrimp will become rubbery. Serve immediately.

name: Smoked Pork Chops

steps: Preheat the smoker to 250 degrees F (120 degrees C). Add wood chips according to the manufacturer's directions.. Place pork chops, unstacked, onto smoker grate. Smoke for 2 hours 30 minutes. Remove chops from the smoker and let rest for 10 minutes.

name: Roasted Leg of Pork

steps: Preheat the oven to 430 degrees F (220 degrees C).. Combine olive oil, sage, garlic powder, onion powder, and salt in a small bowl.. Rinse pork leg and pat dry with a paper towel. Rub seasoned olive oil all over pork leg.. Slice onion and separate layers into rings. Place onion rings and garlic halves into the bottom of a roaster. Place pork on top of onion and garlic.. Roast in the preheated oven for 40 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 355 degrees F (180 degrees C) and continue roasting until an instant-read thermometer inserted into the center reads at least 145 degrees F (63 degrees C), about 1 hour 20 minutes more.. Let pork rest for 5 minutes, then slice for serving.

name: Keto Tuna Salad

steps: Combine water-packed tuna, oil-packed tuna, mayonnaise, celery, red onion, lime juice, mustard, salt, and pepper in a bowl. Mix well.

name: Boneless Turkey Breast in the Instant Pot®
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'ground paprika'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'herbes de Provence'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'seasoned salt'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(3 pound)', 'name': 'frozen boneless turkey breast in mesh, thawed, with gravy packet reserved'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'extra-virgin olive oil, divided'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chicken stock'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'stalks', 'name': 'celery, cut into 4-inch pieces'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, cut into 1/2-inch slices'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}
steps: Combine paprika, herbes de Provence, seasoned salt, salt, and pepper in a small bowl. Place the trivet of a multi-functional pressure cooker (such as Instant Pot®) on a work surface.. Pat all sides of thawed turkey breast with paper towels until dry. Be sure to leave the mesh in place, as this holds the turkey together. Rub turkey with about 2 teaspoons olive oil, then rub with dry seasonings. Set gravy packet aside for later use.. Turn on the cooker and select Saute function. Allow the inner pot to heat, 1 to 2 minutes. Add remaining oil to the hot pot, then add turkey breast and brown on all sides, about 5 minutes. Carefully remove turkey breast and set on the trivet. Pour chicken stock into the hot pot and scrape up any browned bits with a wooden spoon. Place the trivet and turkey breast into the pot and place celery and onions around it. Cancel Saute function.. Close and lock the lid, set the valve to seal, and select high pressure according to manufacturer's instructions. Set timer for 25 minutes. Allow 10 to 15 minutes for pressure to build.. Release pressure using the natural-release method according to manufacturer's instructions, about 15 minutes. Release any remaining pressure carefully using the quick-release method according to manufacturer's instructions.. Open the pot and check internal temperature of the turkey with an instant-read thermometer. Safe internal temperature is at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C). Lift turkey out of the pot and place on a cutting board; cover with aluminum foil. Remove the trivet and turn off the cooker.. Strain cooking liquid into a glass measuring cup. Add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.. Return the inner pot to the cooker, add butter, and select Saute function. Sprinkle flour into the melted butter and whisk briskly to avoid lumps. Whisk bubbling mixture for about 2 minutes, then gradually add the cooking liquid, stirring constantly. Pour in the contents of the gravy packet; cook and stir until mixture comes to a boil and thickens slightly, 5 to 10 minutes. Cancel Saute function and pour gravy into a serving container.. Slice turkey and serve warm with gravy.

name: Lemon-Garlic Air Fryer Salmon
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'melted butter'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'minced garlic'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(6 ounce) fillets', 'name': 'center-cut salmon fillets with skin'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'lemon-pepper seasoning'}, {'quantity': '⅛', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried parsley'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'thin slices', 'name': 'lemon, cut in half'}
steps: Preheat the air fryer to 390 degrees F (200 degrees C).. Combine melted butter and minced garlic in a small bowl.. Rinse salmon fillets and dry with a paper towel. Brush with butter mixture and sprinkle with lemon-pepper seasoning and parsley.. Spray the basket of the air fryer with cooking spray. Place salmon fillets in the basket, skin-side down, and top each with 3 lemon halves.. Cook in the preheated air fryer for 8 to 10 minutes. Remove from the air fryer and let rest for 2 minutes before serving.

name: Crispy Fried Chicken Skin
ingredients: {'quantity': '5', 'unit': '', 'name': 'chicken leg quarters, raw skin only'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'vegetable oil for frying'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt to taste'}
steps: Place chicken skins in a large stockpot. Cover with water. Bring to a boil and cook for 10 minutes. Drain and transfer to a cutting board. Using a sharp knife, scrape off excess fat and cut skin into 1/2-inch wide strips.. Place skin on a baking sheet and refrigerate, uncovered, for at least 8 hours.. Heat oil in a large stockpot to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lower a handful of skins carefully into the hot oil. Fry until crisp, about 4 minutes. Transfer to a plate lined with paper towels to drain and sprinkle with salt. Repeat with remaining chicken skin.

name: Instant Pot Roasted Whole Chicken
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(5 pound)', 'name': 'roasting chicken, rinsed, giblets removed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'dried rosemary, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'dried parsley, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'extra-virgin olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chicken stock'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'cornstarch (Optional)'}
steps: Rub chicken on all sides with salt, pepper, garlic powder, rosemary, and parsley.. Turn on a multi-functional pressure cooker (such as Instant Pot), add olive oil, and select the Sauté function. When hot, add chicken, breast-side down. Cook until skin is browned, about 5 minutes. Use tongs to flip chicken and brown on the other side for 5 more minutes. Carefully remove chicken from the pot and set aside. Pour in chicken stock and deglaze the pan, scraping off all the browned bits. Turn off the Sauté function.. Place the rack insert into the pot and place chicken on the rack, breast-side up. Close and lock the lid. Select the Poultry setting and set the timer for 28 minutes. Allow 10 to 15 minutes for pressure to build.. Release pressure using the natural-release method according to manufacturer's instructions, 10 to 40 minutes. Unlock and remove the lid. Carefully remove chicken to a carving board to rest.. Turn on the Sauté function and whisk cornstarch into the pot with the stock and drippings to make a gravy.

name: Keto Fathead Bread

steps: Beat egg in a medium bowl. Mix Parmesan cheese, almond flour, salt, pepper, and garlic powder together in a second bowl.. Season pork chops with salt and pepper on both sides. steps: Gather all ingredients.. Place pork chops onto a plate and lightly spray both sides with cooking spray..
